features: 【Unique Vertical & Ergonomic 60º Natural Handshake Posture】Compared to traditional horizontal mice, MicroPack new upgrade mouse with silent clicks is meticulously crafted with vertical shape, adopt an ergonomic design that can naturally adapt to the natural posture of the human palm. It reduces strain and fatigue in the wrist, forearm and arm, helping users maintain a comfortable and healthy working state.

【High Precise Tacking & 3 Adjustable DPI】This comfortable mouse with natural grip achieves high-precision cursor control, providing a smoother mouse operation experience. Multiple adjustable sensitivity settings up to 1600 DPI can adjust the speed and accuracy of the mouse, easily switch DPI with a simple press of the switch, making it ideal for gaming, design work, and other demanding tasks.

【Auto-Sleep Power Saving Mode For Long Battery Life】Thanks to the automatic sleep function, our durable mice with smooth scrolling can automatically enter sleep mode after 60s of staying idle to preserve battery. Only a AA battery needed, it can work up to 8 months. (Battery not included); This reliable WIRELESS MOUSE allow you to get rid of messy cords, providing a more flexible working experience.

【Silent Buttons & Wide Compatibility】MicroPack long lasting grip comfort mouse with USB A & Type-C Receiver is compatible with multiple operating systems, including Windows, Mac OS, Linux, etc. Noise-reducing buttons make it suitable for office, home, gaming, shared workspaces or quiet environments.

【Forward And Backword Button】The dedicated forward and backward buttons offer a convenient and efficient means of navigation. Our user friendly vertical mouse is made of high-quality materials, with excellent durability and reliability, and can work stably for a long time. Please note that the product cannot be programmed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Love this mouse!! The color shows as a mint color on Amazon but is really more of a sage color which was a very pleasant surprise, feels nice on my wrist, very quiet clicks. Easy to connect to iPad and computer just plug it in! Arrived on Saturday and I’ve used it like crazy since then. Definitely worth trying! :)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 19, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Relief for hand pain. Working great so far!
reviews.reviewText: I've been using a kensington trackball for many years. I've been having some recent hand and wrist pain that settles in my thumb. My physical therapist suggested a vertical mouse, and I decided to order this since it looked comfortable and has great reviews and a great price. The optical sensor on this is better than any other I've tried. It works great so far on various surfaces, the sensor, buttons and travel are all working great right out of the box. The glide is very good too. The next test will be to see how long this lasts. At this price I'm really blown away by the quality of this.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Take minor adjustment to get used to, but initial feeling is great
reviews.reviewText: My logi mouse went crazy and needed a replacement, plus my hand hurt after long use, so I started looking for a vertical mouse. The Logi Lift is a natural candidate, but this cheaper alternative is quite intriguing, so I decided to give it a try before I buy the more expensive Logi. This one seems a keeper. Hand hold feel very comfortable.Initially, I feel my hand has to move a lot more to get the mouse move (for not so precise work), but after I adjusted the DPI setting, it seems more responsive now. Still feel more time to get used to, but no significant negative feeling. The click is very light and quiet, if that is what you looking for. I used it at home and somewhat prefer stronger click feedback. But again, I see he benefit of quiet operation as well.Don't know how long this will last. However, even the more expensive Logi will break eventually. So, my initial feeling of this product is very positive. Will update if things change.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 25, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Comfort is extremely well! Defiantly helps with Severe wrist pain. Down fall it does not work at all with a mouse pad, or leather like mouse pad. The mouse only works on laminate type surface, does not work on a desk surface or table top. The clicks are quite which is a huge pls but the main issue was the mouse left click does not seem to register the first 2/3 times and that the most needed part. Could be that it’s defective, stuff like that does happen nothing is perfect. Scroll wheel works great! Really wished it work to its full potential. Will update with replacement

reviews.reviewText: This is a great product! I haven’t had to change the batteries and it’s been a very long time. It’s very comfortable! The clicks are so soft, and can’t hear any sounds.

reviews.reviewText: This mouse is ergonomically designed and definitely eases the wrist and arm strain of gaming. It was a treasured item until the spinner stopped working less than a month in.
